HOUSE BILL 1264
J1 6lr2010
CF SB 798
By: Delegates Hill, Lopez, Alston, Guzzone, Ross, Ruth, and Woods
Introduced and read first time: February 12, 2026
Assigned to: Health
A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Public Health – Maryland Medical Assistance Program – Tobacco Cessation
3 FOR the purpose of requiring the Maryland Medical Assistance Program to provide, subject
4 to the limitations of the State budget and as permitted by federal law, individual and
5 group counseling for the purpose of tobacco cessation; prohibiting the Program and
6 managed care organizations from requiring prior authorization for any product or
7 service for use in tobacco cessation; and generally relating to the Maryland Medical
8 Assistance Program and tobacco cessation.
9 BY repealing and reenacting, without amendments,
10 Article – Health – General
11 Section 15–103(a)(1)
12 Annotated Code of Maryland
13 (2023 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
14 BY repealing and reenacting, with amendments,
15 Article – Health – General
16 Section 15–103(a)(2)(xxvii) and (xxviii)
17 Annotated Code of Maryland
18 (2023 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
19 BY adding to
20 Article – Health – General
21 Section 15–103(a)(2)(xxix) and 15–160
22 Annotated Code of Maryland
23 (2023 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
24 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
25 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
26 Article – Health – General
