2 HOUSE BILL 1264
1 15–103.
2 (a) (1) The Secretary shall administer the Maryland Medical Assistance
3 Program.
4 (2) The Program:
5 (xxvii) Beginning on January 1, 2026, if providing coverage for
6 the delivery of anesthesia, shall provide coverage for the delivery of anesthesia in
7 accordance with § 15–862 of the Insurance Article; [and]
8 (xxviii) Beginning on January 1, 2026, shall provide calcium score
9 testing in accordance with § 15–863 of the Insurance Article; AND
10 (XXIX) SHALL PROVIDE, SUBJECT TO THE LIMITATIONS OF
11 THE STATE BUDGET, AND AS PERMITTED BY FEDERAL LAW, INDIVIDUAL AND GROUP
12 COUNSELING FOR THE PURPOSE OF TOBACCO CESSATION.
13 15–160.
14 THE PROGRAM AND A MANAGED CARE ORGANIZATION MAY NOT REQUIRE A
15 PRIOR AUTHORIZATION FOR ANY PRODUCT OR SERVICE FOR USE IN ELIMINATING
16 AN INDIVIDUAL’S DEPENDENCE ON TOBACCO.
17 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
18 October 1, 2026.

